Key Match Events: John Collins scored 28 points and made a game-winning dunk with 6.4 seconds remaining to lift the Utah Jazz to a 115-113 win over the Dallas Mavericks.
Naji Marshall missed a corner 3-pointer at the buzzer, resulting in a loss for the Mavericks.
Jordan Clarkson added 20 points for the Jazz and his bullet pass set up Collins' game-winner.
Luka Doncic led all scorers with 37 points, nine assists, and seven rebounds.
Klay Thompson tied the game with one of his five 3-pointers, finishing with 17 points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Utah picked up its first home win in six games this season.
The Jazz were off to their worst home start since the franchise's inaugural 1974-75 season in New Orleans.
Dallas Mavericks played without Kyrie Irving due to a strained right shoulder.
